  "issue_number": 12409,
  "issue_title": "[Feature Request]: configure system setting",
  "issue_body": "### Self Checks\n\n- [x] I have searched for existing issues [search for existing issues](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues), including closed ones.\n- [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Non-english title submitions will be closed directly ( \u975e\u82f1\u6587\u6807\u9898\u7684\u63d0\u4ea4\u5c06\u4f1a\u88ab\u76f4\u63a5\u5173\u95ed ) ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Please do not modify this template :) and fill in all the required fields.\n\n### Is your feature request related to a problem?\n\n```Markdown\n\n```\n\n### Describe the feature you'd like\n\nImplement a comprehensive set of commands to manage system variables through the admin CLI interface with the following functionality:\n\n1. List All Variables\nCommand: list vars;\n\nDisplays all system variables in a formatted table\n\nShows columns: data_type, name, setting_type, value\n\nSupports pagination (if applicable)\n\n2. Filter Variables by Prefix\nCommand: show var <prefix>;\n\nDisplays variables matching the specified prefix\n\nExample: show var mail; shows all mail-related configurations\n\nMaintains the same table format as list vars\n\n3. View Specific Variable\nCommand: show var <full_variable_name>;\n\nDisplays detailed information for a single variable\n\nExample: show var mail.server; shows only the mail server configuration\n\n4. Modify Variable Values\nCommand: set var <variable_name> <new_value>;\n\nUpdates the specified variable with the new value\n\nReturns confirmation message: \"Set variable successfully\"\n\nExample: set var mail.server localhost;\n\nShould include validation based on data_type (string, integer, bool)\n\n```\nadmin> list vars;\n+-----------+---------------------+--------------+-----------+\n| data_type | name                | setting_type | value     |\n+-----------+---------------------+--------------+-----------+\n| string    | default_role        | config       | user      |\n| bool      | enable_whitelist    | config       | true      |\n| string    | mail.default_sender | config       |           |\n| string    | mail.password       | config       |           |\n| integer   | mail.port           | config       | 15        |\n| string    | mail.server         | config       | 127.0.0.1 |\n| integer   | mail.timeout        | config       | 10        |\n| bool      | mail.use_ssl        | config       | true      |\n| bool      | mail.use_tls        | config       | false     |\n| string    | mail.username       | config       |           |\n+-----------+---------------------+--------------+-----------+\n\nadmin> show var mail;\n+-----------+---------------------+--------------+-----------+\n| data_type | name                | setting_type | value     |\n+-----------+---------------------+--------------+-----------+\n| string    | mail.default_sender | config       |           |\n| string    | mail.password       | config       |           |\n| integer   | mail.port           | config       | 15        |\n| string    | mail.server         | config       | 127.0.0.1 |\n| integer   | mail.timeout        | config       | 10        |\n| bool      | mail.use_ssl        | config       | true      |\n| bool      | mail.use_tls        | config       | false     |\n| string    | mail.username       | config       |           |\n+-----------+---------------------+--------------+-----------+\n\nadmin> show var mail.server;\n+-----------+-------------+--------------+-----------+\n| data_type | name        | setting_type | value     |\n+-----------+-------------+--------------+-----------+\n| string    | mail.server | config       | 127.0.0.1 |\n+-----------+-------------+--------------+-----------+\n\nadmin> set var mail.server localhost;\nSet variable successfully\n\nadmin> show var mail.server;\n+-----------+-------------+--------------+-----------+\n| data_type | name        | setting_type | value     |\n+-----------+-------------+--------------+-----------+\n| string    | mail.server | config       | localhost |\n+-----------+-------------+--------------+-----------+\n```\n\n### Describe implementation you've considered\n\n_No response_\n\n### Documentation, adoption, use case\n\n```Markdown\n\n```\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
